AT command sample extension.

 - Handle HTTPS request
 - Verify server's certificate

Usage:

AT+GETTEST="hostname",[0|1],[0|1]

 1st arg: target hostname to send "GET /" request

 2nd arg: 0 -> send HTTP request to port 80
          1 -> send HTTPS request to port 443

 * for HTTPS *
 3rd arg: 0 -> disable server certificate verification
          1 -> enable server certificate verification


See http://dsas.blog.klab.org/archives/52223926.html
(Japanese only)
